[3] Angola (KS)
Date: Tue 26 Jul 2011
Source: allAfrica.com [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201107270032.html


Health authorities in the municipality of Amboim, Kwanza Sul province,
registered a reduction of 38 cases of measles in the 2nd quarter of
this year [2011], fruit of the vaccination campaigns held in the
district. The cases of measles, according to the supervisor of public
health and control of endemic diseases, J. Alfinete, decreased from 40
to only 2 cases. He said that 2 children are hospitalised with measles
and are receiving treatment at the municipal hospital of Amboim.
[Their condition is satisfactory].

